CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1963, pg. 11, reads: "Sign of Times - To aid motorists on the Parkway East and West, the state has ordered scores of new directional signs. Shown above, installing one at the intersection close by Squirrel Hill tunnels, are (standing left to right) Charlie Brown of Braddock and Same Mete of North Side, and (on ladder, left to right) Glenn Yeager and Tom Boyle, both of Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Glenn Yeager and Tom Boyle on ladders, and Charlie Brown and Sam Mete on ground, installing signs on Route 376 Parkway near Squirrel Hill tunnels, another version
